icate<ul><li>having at least 1 year’s practical experience in the field of soil corrosion, obtained within the 5 years preceding the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>or have obtained at least a <strong>secondary education qualification</strong> or an equivalent certificate<ul><li>having at least 5 years’ practical experience in the field of soil corrosion, obtained within the 10 years preceding the application for recognition.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h2><strong>Validity period and obligations</strong></h2><p>The recognition is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. As an ‘environmental expert in soil corrosion’, you must meet the following obligations among others to retain your recognition:</p><ul><li>hold <strong>insurance </strong>for third-party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li><li>pay the <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/vlarel-retributies\">annual fee</a>. The first payment is to be made in the year following the year in which you obtained the recognition. Failure to pay the annual fee will lead to automatic suspension of the recognition following a formal notice of default. If the fee is not paid within 30 days of the suspension, the recognition will automatically lapse</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-milieudeskundige-bodemcorrosie\">More info on the obligations for recognised environmental experts</a></p>"},"naam":{"en":"Requirements","nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"Voorwaarden","nl-BE-x-generated-formal":"Voorwaarden","nl":"Voorwaarden"},"@type":"Voorwaarde","order":0}],"procedures":[{"naam":{"nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"Procedure","nl":"Procedure","en":"Procedure","nl-BE-x-generated-formal":"Procedure"},"beschrijving":{"nl":"<p>Vraag uw erkenning aan bij het Departement Omgeving van de Vlaamse overheid.</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://assets.vlaanderen.be/raw/upload/v1652793323/200204_Aanvraag_erkenning_milieudeskundige_bodem